videos.description: Davion Mitchell steals the ball and gets it to Jared Butler, who finishes with the  nice score for Baylor.

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Davion Mitchell's steal leads to a Jared Butler layup) 2020/3/7

videos.headline: Davion Mitchell's steal leads to a Jared Butler layup

videos.description: Sean McNeil drains a 3-pointer to increase West Virginia's lead over Baylor.

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (McNeil pads WVU's lead with a 3-pointer) 2020/3/7

videos.headline: McNeil pads WVU's lead with a 3-pointer

videos.description: Mark Vital misses his free throw, but he muscles his way in to grab the rebound and score the Baylor bucket.

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Vital makes up for missed FT with a bucket) 2020/3/7

videos.headline: Vital makes up for missed FT with a bucket

videos.description: Sean McNeil passes to Emmitt Matthews Jr., who finishes with a dunk for West Virginia.

videos.headline: Matthews increases WVU's lead with a dunk

videos.description: West Virginia steals the ball away from Baylor. Going the other way, Miles McBride gets the ball and finishes with a one-handed jam.

videos.headline: McBride throws it down with authority for WVU

videos.description: West Virginia's fans storm the court after the Mountaineers defeat No. 4 Baylor 76-64.
